    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "it's not just the quiet. it's like the color has been sucked out of everything. i look at the garden or the lamp or even my own hands and it feels like i'm watching a movie of someone else's life. i'm just going through the motions but there's nothing left in me. i feel like i'm just waiting for something to happen, but nothing ever does. i just want the heaviness to stop.",
